    <title ixia_locid="55">Editing Interface Settings</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="56">You can change the settings for a host interface.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="57">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N1001E_N1001B_N10001" ixia_locid="58">
            <p ixia_locid="59">The ability to change the interface settings is especially useful for
                updating the management interface. When a compute node is first created, its
                internal management interface is automatically set up using the default <nameliteral ixia_locid="70">Interface Type</nameliteral> (<nameliteral ixia_locid="71">ethernet</nameliteral>). If you are using <draft-comment author="jmaran" ixia_locid="206">What
                    is "LAG"?</draft-comment>LAG on the internal management network, you must update
                this manually to <nameliteral ixia_locid="72">aggregated
                    ethernet</nameliteral>.<draft-comment author="jmaran" ixia_locid="207">Assuming that "ethernet"
                    is lowercase in the UI or setting where these are selected. Otherwise, make
                    uppercase (and file a bug against the UI to get them to change it to "Ethernet"
                    unless it must be all lowercase for a technical reason). </draft-comment></p>
            <p ixia_locid="82">You can also edit an internal management or infrastructure interface
                to attach to a data network by selecting <uicontrol ixia_locid="192">data</uicontrol>
                as an additional Network Type for the interface, or using the CLI. For CLI
                instructions, see <xref href="jow1427029415968.xml" ixia_locid="193"/>.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="90"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="91">US62814
                    added</draft-comment><draft-comment author="jmaran" ixia_locid="208">This xref is local in the
                    sys admin guide but interbook when this topic appears in the installation guide.
                    Updated to interbook reference.</draft-comment>To add or edit IP addresses on a
                data interface, see <ph ixia_locid="209" otherprops="printonly"><cite ixia_locid="210">Titanium Server System
                        Administration: </cite></ph><cite ixia_locid="211"><ph ixia_locid="212"><xref href="jow1443038432894.xml" ixia_locid="92"/></ph></cite>.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/lock_host" id="step_N1003F_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="73">
                <cmd ixia_locid="74"/>
            </step>
            <step conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/open_details_locked_host" id="step_N10048_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="75">
                <cmd ixia_locid="76"/>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10069_N10028_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="20">
                <cmd ixia_locid="21">Select the<uicontrol ixia_locid="22"> Interfaces</uicontrol>
                    tab to display the existing interfaces.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="200">
                    <fig id="fig_N10076_N10073_N10064_N1004B_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="201">
                        <image alt="Interfaces list" href="rst1440770718462.image" ixia_locid="202"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N1009A_N10027_N1001B_N10001" ixia_locid="60">
                <cmd ixia_locid="61">Click <uicontrol ixia_locid="62">Edit Interface</uicontrol> for the interface you want to
                    change.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="63">
                    <fig id="fig_xfz_5fm_vp" ixia_locid="64">
                        <image alt="TiS Edit Interface" href="jow1426954976474.image" id="image_w5l_tlk_lr" ixia_locid="24"/>
                    </fig>
                    <!-- p>If you are changing the <nameliteral>Interface Type</nameliteral> to
                            <nameliteral>aggregated ethernet</nameliteral>, select the second port
                        connected to the network.</p -->
                    <!-- JO 2015-03-24 screenshot? sounds plausible, but I don't see a second port -->
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100BB_N10027_N1001B_N10001" ixia_locid="67">
                <cmd ixia_locid="68">Make the required changes, and then click <uicontrol ixia_locid="69">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="79">
                    <p ixia_locid="80">The settings shown depend on the interface type. For
                        information about the available settings, see <xref href="jow1426955886080.xml" ixia_locid="81"/>.</p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100B2_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="77">
                <cmd ixia_locid="78">Unlock the host.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
